HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 630
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to commend Tricia Herzfeld for her honorable
service as a member of the Davidson County
Election Commission.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to
improving the quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Tricia Herzfeld is one such estimable person who evinces the greatest
integrity and probity in all her chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, having served with distinction since 2013 as a member of the Davidson
County Election Commission, Ms. Herzfeld is taking her well-deserved retirement from that
esteemed body; and
WHEREAS, a founding partner at Herzfeld, Suetholz, Gastel, Leniski and Wall, PLLC,
Tricia Herzfeld has established herself as one of Tennessee's foremost attorneys, representing
clients in complex and high-profile litigation in both state and federal courts; and
WHEREAS, her legal work has addressed vital issues in the areas of sexual assault,
harassment and discrimination, free speech, freedom of religion, equal protection, immigrants'
rights, and racial profiling, which have led to multi-million-dollar settlements on behalf of those
whose rights have been violated; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Herzfeld earned her undergraduate degree from George Washington
University and her law degree from George Washington School of Law; she is also a graduate
of the 2010 Tennessee Bar Association Leadership Law program; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of her tireless advocacy, Tricia Herzfeld and her colleagues
received the 2022 Outstanding Trial Lawyer of the Year Award from the Tennessee Trial
Lawyers Association for their work on opioid litigation on behalf of cities and counties in Upper
East Tennessee; and
